  "response": "## Reading the finding\n\nFrom `crime_00001` (`svg_with_embedded_raster`, severity **high**):\n\n- **Number of embedded rasters:** \"**2** `<image href=\\\"data:image/…;base64,…\\\">` occurrences\"\n- **MIME types:** \"embedded MIME types: **image/jpeg, image/png**\"\n\nThe SVG is 592 bytes total — the base64 payloads dominate that, since plain vector geometry would be far smaller. The suggested action is \"re-author the raster region as vector paths, or split it out to its own asset.\"\n\n## Remediation plan\n\nThe two embeds almost certainly correspond to different layer types and want different fixes:\n\n**1. The `image/png` raster → re-author as vector paths.**\nPNGs embedded in a logo SVG are typically pre-flattened vector art (an icon, a mark, or a wordmark that was rasterized on export). The source vectors usually still exist in the design tool. Re-open `partner-logo.svg`'s source in Figma/Illustrator/Sketch, find the PNG layer, and re-export with that layer kept as native shapes. The result inside the SVG is `<path>` / `<rect>` / `<circle>` / `<text>` — no `<image>`.\n\n**2. The `image/jpeg` raster → split out to a standalone asset.**\nJPEG inside an SVG signals photographic content (a partner headshot, a product photo, a complex gradient flattened to a photo). That genuinely can't be vectorized without losing fidelity, so don't try. Two options:\n\n- **Preferred:** drop it from the logo entirely if it's decorative — most partner logos are mark + wordmark and don't need a photo baked in.\n- **If the photo is part of the brand:** extract it to `src/assets/partner-logo-photo.webp` (re-encoded to WebP/AVIF to keep page weight down) and have the *consuming page* render both assets side-by-side — the SVG for the logo, the `<img>` for the photo. Keeping the raster inside the SVG via `<image href=\"./partner-logo-photo.webp\">` is technically possible but pointless: the SVG no longer scales cleanly anyway, so the wrapper adds no value.\n\n## Files after the refactor\n\n- **`src/assets/partner-logo.svg`** — vector-only: `<svg>` containing `<path>`, `<rect>`, `<text>`, `<linearGradient>` etc. **Zero `<image>` tags, zero `data:` URIs.**\n- **`src/assets/partner-logo-photo.webp`** *(only if the JPEG content is keep-worthy)* — a standalone modern-format raster, referenced from the page that needs both, not from inside the SVG.\n\nThe file stays, the logo still ships, and `crimes scan` should drop `crime_00001` on the next run.",
